thread.title: Oregon State Beavers picked to win Pac-12 in women's basketball preseason coaches poll
thread.title_full: Oregon State Beavers picked to win Pac-12 in women's basketball preseason coaches poll | OregonLive.com

author: Gina Mizell | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Oregon State Beavers picked to win Pac-12 in women's basketball preseason coaches poll
text:
Oregon State has been picked to repeat as women's basketball Pac-12 champions, according to the preseason coaches poll released Wednesday at Pac-12 Media Days in San Francisco.
The Beavers won the regular-season conference title last season and return four starters, including All-Pac-12 performers Ruth Hamblin, Jamie Weisner and Sydney Wiese. Scott Rueck is also the reigning Pac-12 Coach of the Year.
OSU received the maximum first-place votes (11) and 121 total points. The selection is also a historic one, as it's the first time in the preseason coaches poll's 15-year history that Stanford was not picked to win the league. The Cardinal is projected to finish second (104 points), while Arizona State is picked third (102 points, one first-place vote).
Here's the full Pac-12 preseason coaches poll:
1. Oregon State (11) 121 points
2. Stanford 104 points
3. Arizona State (1) 102 points
T4. California 88 points
T4. UCLA 88 points
6. Washington 68 points
7. USC 60 points
8. Oregon 52 points
9. Colorado 39 points
10. Washington State 30 points
11. Utah 23 points
12. Arizona 17 points
-- Gina Mizell | @ginamizell
